 reasoning, or <think> sections in your response. \\nGo directly to the XML response format without any preamble or explanation.\\n\\nRespond using XML format like this:\\n<response>\\n    <thought>Your thought here</thought>\\n    <actions>ACTION1,ACTION2</actions>\\n    <providers>PROVIDER1,PROVIDER2</providers>\\n    <text>Your response text here</text>\\n</response>\\n\\nIMPORTANT: Your response must ONLY contain the <response></response> XML block above. Do not include any text, thinking, or reasoning before or after this XML block. Start your response immediately with <response> and end with </response>.\\n</output>", "modelKey": "TEXT_LARGE", "provider": "openai", "response": "<response>\\n    <thought>The user is interested in the application of eco credits in Red Hook, Brooklyn. I'll provide examples of how eco credits can be utilized for community and ecological benefits in this area.</thought>\\n    <actions>REPLY</actions>\\n    <providers></providers>\\n    <text>Eco credits could play a transformative role in Red Hook by supporting projects that enhance both ecology and community resilience. 🌿 For instance, they might fund green infrastructure like rooftop gardens or permeable pavements that help manage stormwater runoff and reduce urban heat effects. Investing these credits into solar panel installations on community buildings could lower energy costs while contributing to carbon reductions. Furthermore, supporting local initiatives aimed at restoring native plant species can improve biodiversity and create natural buffers against flooding. Each credit isn't just a number; it's an investment in building a sustainable future for Red Hook, ensuring the neighborhood remains vibrant and resilient amid environmental challenges.</text>\\n</response>", "modelType": "TEXT_LARGE", "timestamp": 1754673494644, "executionTime": 10273.279693000019}	useModel:TEXT_LARGE	7de19cb6-ad0e-0a27-b290-9bd52b248847
